            <para>
                <emph type="bold">Parts Affected</emph>
            </para>
            <para>New and revised parts for the flywheel housing assembly are as follows (Refer to
                <hotlnk xrefid="f98120201">Exploded View of Front and Rear Mounting Brackets And Flywheel Housing
                    <xref refid="f98120201"/>
                </hotlnk>
                for part locations):
            </para>
            <figure id="f98120201" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic filename="../tsifigures/EG3729.webp" type="webp" box="yes"/>
                <caption>Figure 1. Exploded View of Front and Rear Mounting Brackets And Flywheel Housing</caption>
                <calloutgroup>
                    <callout1>Front Engine Mounting Bracket</callout1>
                    <callout1>Special Bolt Flange</callout1>
                    <callout1>Snubber Insulator</callout1>
                    <callout1>O-Ring</callout1>
                    <callout1>Flywheel Housing (Without Service Access Cover)</callout1>
                    <callout1>Rear Engine Mounting Bracket, R.H.</callout1>
                    <callout1>Flywheel Housing Baffle (Used on Flywheel Housing Without Service Access Cover)</callout1>
                    <callout1>Rear Engine Mounting Bracket, L.H.</callout1>
                    <callout1>Cap Plug (Used on Flywheel Housing Without Service Access Cover)</callout1>
                    <callout1>Flywheel Housing Plate Cover</callout1>
                    <callout1>Service Access Cover</callout1>
                    <callout1>Flywheel Housing (With Service Access Cover)</callout1>
                    <callout1>Flywheel Housing Baffle (Used on Flywheel Housing with Service Access Cover)</callout1>
                </calloutgroup>
            </figure>
            <para>
                <emph type="bold">SERVICE PROCEDURE</emph>
            </para>
            <para>The service procedure for removal and installation of the flywheel housing remains the same. Refer to
                Service Manual, EGES 120 for further information.
            </para>
        </svcproc>
    </tsi>
</isis>
